{
    "id": 20137,
    "title": "Opinion Announcement - May 12, 1997",
    "transcript": {
        "title": null,
        "duration": 119.606,
        "sections": [
            {
                "start": 0,
                "stop": 119.606,
                "byte_start": 28672,
                "byte_stop": 507026,
                "turns": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "stop": 119.606,
                        "byte_start": 28672,
                        "byte_stop": 507026,
                        "speaker": null,
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 3.507,
                                "byte_start": 28672,
                                "byte_stop": 42778,
                                "text": "I have the opinions of the Court to announce in two cases."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 3.507,
                                "stop": 7.268,
                                "byte_start": 42778,
                                "byte_stop": 57825,
                                "text": "The first is Harbor Tug versus Papai."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 7.268,
                                "stop": 16.125,
                                "byte_start": 57825,
                                "byte_stop": 93247,
                                "text": "Here, the respondent, John Papai, was injured while working on a tugboat, owned by the -- owned an operator by the petitioner, the Harbor Tug Company."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 16.125,
                                "stop": 18.901,
                                "byte_start": 93247,
                                "byte_stop": 104323,
                                "text": "He was painting the vessel at dockside."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 18.901,
                                "stop": 21.969,
                                "byte_start": 104323,
                                "byte_stop": 116652,
                                "text": "He claimed he was a seaman under the Jones Act."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 21.969,
                                "stop": 28.814,
                                "byte_start": 116652,
                                "byte_stop": 144029,
                                "text": "The employer insisted he was an employee under the Longshoremen and Harbor Workers\u0027 Compensation Act."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 28.814,
                                "stop": 47.528,
                                "byte_start": 144029,
                                "byte_stop": 218843,
                                "text": "The reason for a dispute like this is because the Jones Act provides a much more liberal recovery in damages for an injured person than the Longshoremen and Harbor Workers\u0027 Act, which is more like Workmen\u0027s Compensation with just a scheduled set of payment for scheduled injuries."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 47.528,
                                "stop": 55.788,
                                "byte_start": 218843,
                                "byte_stop": 251862,
                                "text": "In an opinion authored by Justice Kennedy, and filed with the clerk today, we hold that Papai\u0027s showing of coverage under the Jones Act was insufficient."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 55.788,
                                "stop": 62.276,
                                "byte_start": 251862,
                                "byte_stop": 277880,
                                "text": "The seamen\u0027s status issue requires us to refer to our decision in an earlier case entitled \u201cChandris.\u201d"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 62.276,
                                "stop": 72.659,
                                "byte_start": 277880,
                                "byte_stop": 319363,
                                "text": "In Chandris, we said that a worker can establish seamen status based on the substantiality of his connection to an identifiable group of vessels."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 72.659,
                                "stop": 88.626,
                                "byte_start": 319363,
                                "byte_stop": 383206,
                                "text": "In this case, it was Papai\u0027s theory that he had a substantial connection to a group of vessels since over a two and a quarter year period, he worked for several vessels through the same hiring hall, though they were owned by several different employers."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 88.626,
                                "stop": 95.853,
                                "byte_start": 383206,
                                "byte_stop": 412150,
                                "text": "In his view, it made no difference that the three employers were not linked by any common ownership or control."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 95.853,
                                "stop": 102.372,
                                "byte_start": 412150,
                                "byte_stop": 438168,
                                "text": "We disagree with that interpretation of the phrase \u201cidentifiable group of vessels\u201d as used in Chandris."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 102.372,
                                "stop": 112.544,
                                "byte_start": 438168,
                                "byte_stop": 478919,
                                "text": "Vessels have to be subject to common ownership or control to constitute an identifiable group, so that we reverse the judgment of the Court of Appeals."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 112.544,
                                "stop": 119.606,
                                "byte_start": 478919,
                                "byte_stop": 507026,
                                "text": "Justice Stevens has filed a dissenting opinion in which Justices Ginsburg and Breyer joined."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    },
